@NODE EG-0.0 "E!-PAGER v1.20 Documentation - Description and Updates"

 DESCRIPTION =============================================================

  E!-PAGER is a complete replacement for the chat and pager in EXCELSIOR!
  bulletin board system. There are many advanced options, allowing you to
  customize the pager suitable for your needs. You can use speech and ex-
  ternal sample players to get your attention when someone is paging you,
  using some module player would also be possible. ANSI split screen chat
  allows you to use separate windows for you and the user while chatting.


 UPDATES =================================================================
  
  If you are upgrading from an older version than 1.20, you should remove
  all pager files and install the new version from the beginning. You can
  save your DATA/PagerNotice because the format has not been changed. All
  minor future releases will be described in the CHANGES.DOC file.
@ENDNODE
@NODE EG-1.0 "E!-PAGER v1.20 Documentation - Distribution and Registration"

 DISTRIBUTION ============================================================

  E!-PAGER v1.20 and future versions are distributed under the concept of
  shareware. This means you must either register or discontinue using the
  program after twenty days of evaluation. Registration trough the author
  is only way to become a registered user, here is how to do it properly.

  Send euther five ($5) US dollars or twenty (20 FIM) Finnish marks to me
  and you will be able to dowload your personal keyfile from my BBS after
  I've received the money. I can only accept cash, and only in currencies
  mentioned above, no money orders or cheques please. If you'd like me to
  send you the keyfile and the latest version via normal mail, please add
  another $5 USD or 20 FIM for shipping. Remember to include your address
  and real name, short letter about yourself would also be very nice, but
  optional.

  Keyfile will disable the one minute time limit in chat and display your
  name and serial number before paging. You can distribute the evaluation
  release as long as the archive and all files remain intact, but you may
  not distribute, sell or edit the keyfile under any conditions.

  Registration                 $5 USD or 20 FIM
  Disk & Shipping (optional)   $5 USD or 20 FIM
                              -----------------
                              $10 USD or 40 FIM

  My address can be found from the @{" Credits and Comments " link EG-5.0} section.

 DISCLAIMER ==============================================================

  There is no warranty or guarantee that this program is entirely free of
  bugs. All possible risks and damages arising through the use, misuse or
  inability of this program, are at the resposibility of the user.
@ENDNODE
@NODE EG-2.0 "E!-PAGER v1.20 Documentation - Installation and Configuration Options"

 INSTALLATION ============================================================

  You can place all binaries and text files where ever you wish, I perso-
  nally would put them to DOORS:PAGER directory. The registration keyfile
  must be found from the BBS:DATA, otherwise pager will run in the evalu-
  ation mode. After you've moved all files to appropriate directories, it
  is time to execute PCONFIG, the configuration program.

  PCONFIG takes no arguments and the graphical user interface is fast and
  easy to learn, you should not have any problems after carefully reading
  the following explanation. Gadgets are marked with a colon here.

        SAVE:   Quits and saves current changes to BBS:DATA/PagerConfig.

       PATHS:   Opens a window for changing the file paths.

      CANCEL:   Quits without saving any possible changes.

                                  * * *

      OPTIONS   These checkbox gadgets are used to customize several chat
                and pager options. Checking a gadget enables the feature.

       BEEPS:   If set, pager will send beep to the user during the page.

      REASON:   If set, user will be prompted for a reason before paging.

     LOG ALL:   If set, all pages including those when you are 'not here'
                will be appended to the log, excluding disabled users.

    ACTIVATE:   If set, the page window will be activated and screen will
                be moved to the front when someone starts to page sysop.

   OVERRIDER:   If not set, Overrider settings are ignored by all utils.

  MOVE FRONT:   If set, BB screen is moved to the front when chat starts.

   ONLY ONCE:   If set, external program, like sample or module player is
                executed only once during the page.

    ANSI BOX:   If set, users will get a box around the reason prompt.    

     PROTECT:   If set, protect is automatically enabled in the chat.

      SPEECH:   If set, pager will use speech to tell you the reason when
                page begins. More about speech is discussed below.

                                  * * *

       SPEECH   E!-PAGER provides very basic support for narrator.device,
                you can use following gadgets to change speech attributes
                and check the one in options box to enable this feature.

        RATE:   The speech rate used, default 150 words per minute.

       PITCH:   The speech pitch used, default 110.

        FREQ:   The speech sampling frequency used, default 22200 Hz.

         SEX:   Either male or female vocal tract can be used.

                                  * * *

    CHAT MODE   This mutually exclusive gadget can be used to select chat
                mode to be used. Split screen chat will automatically de-
                fault to a normal chat with ASCII users.

      SCREEN:   Normal chat, will be opened to the BB screen.

      WINDOW:   Normal chat, will be opened to a window in WB screen.

    EXTERNAL:   Executes an external C-Door specified in the path window.

   PAGE METER   These mutually exclusive gadgets are used to select meter
                for both sysop and the user, these are discussed later.

    FEEDBACK:   Enter a global BBS command to leave feedback here, option
                can also be disabled by leaving this gadget empty.

                                  * * *

      STRING:   This string is used by most of the user page meters, more
                will be discussed later in the page meter section.

       AVAIL:   This gadget contains 24 numbers, each number representing
                the hours from 0 to 23. By changing these numbers you can
                set when you are and when you are not available for chat.

                0: Sysop isn't available.
                1: Sysop should be available.
                2: Sysop wouldn't like to be disturbed.

       TIMES:   How long one page takes if it's not interrupted by sysop,
                each time takes about two seconds and external program is
                executed if ONLY ONCE flag is not enabled.

       LINES:   Split screen chat adjusts both it's windows to fit to the
                sysop's and user's screens.  Height of the sysop's screen
                is specified by moving this slider gadget.

  Pressing the PATHS gadget will open a path setup window, it contains 14
  string gadgets for changing file paths. You can also use ASL requesters
  by pressing the ASL gadgets after each string entry.

   AVAILABLE:   Text displayed when the sysop should be available.

    NOT HERE:   Text displayed when the sysop is not available.

    NOT MOOD:   Text displayed when the sysop is not in the mood to chat.

    ACCEPTED:   Text displayed after an accepted chat request.

     TIMEOUT:   Text displayed after an unsuccesful page.

      REASON:   Text displayed before the reason prompt.

      PAGING:   Text displayed before the page begins.

      DUMPED:   Text displayed after a dumped chat request.

      NOTICE:   Text displayed before notice defined in Overrider.

  These are the text files that you can edit to customize the output. All
  IPL and ANSI codes can be used as well as the .TTx extensions, you have
  the possibility to change anything the pager displays, except copyright
  notices. Few prompts also use some text from the language buffer.

        CHAT:   Full path and command to execute an external C-Door chat.
                You can use any C-Door as a chat, but mainly this is here
                for the included split screen chat.

      PLAYER:   Full path and command to execute the sample player or any
                equivalent program, used to get your attention. You could
                leave this gadget empty if you don't need sample players.

    NOTIFIER:   Full path and command to open the notifier. Notifiers are
                discussed later.

    LOG FILE:   Full path and file name for the log. User name and reason
                are appended here after the page, enter NIL: to disable.

    DISABLED:   Directory for disabled names. If you don't wish that cer-
                tain users page you, create a text file with his/her name 
                to the directory specified here, and when this user tries
                paging you, this file is displayed instead.

  Next and last task is to make the pager available for the users. Either
  you can add it to the doors area as any EXCELSIOR! door, or replace the
  global chat command in the EX.BBSMenus with the following example. This
  will be the easiest way for the users and highly recommended. You might
  also wish to use the included PLOGS program for displaying and deleting
  the pager logs easily from the BBS.

  # RetCode       Command          IsSysOp      AccessGroup       Display
    595,           C,              0,           "1-32",           "\#2BBS:DOORS/PAGER/BIN/PAGER\"
    596,          LP,              1,           "1-32",           "\#2BBS:DOORS/PAGER/BIN/PLOGS\"


 PAGE METERS =============================================================
  
  There are currently four different page meters for the user and two for
  the sysop. Use the configuration program to select your favourite meter
  or disable the feature by selecting option NONE.

         USER   These are displayed to the user through serial port.

        DOTS:   Sends the character specified in the STRING entry as many
                times as specified in the TIMES entry.

     NUMERIC:   Uses numbers to display how many tries are remaining.

   KOLORIFIC:   Displays a colorful bar graph with green, yellow and red.
                Graph grows in lenght and colors change to yellow and red
                when only few page tries are remaining.

  STEPBYSTEP:   Text in STRING entry is sent to the user letter by letter
                revealing the entire sentence slowly. Text shouldn't have
                any ANSI or IPL codes as they might cause some troubles.

      RANDOM:   This will randomly choose one of the four meters. Because
                there is only single STRING entry, it is reserved for the
                STEPBYSTEP meter and DOTS will use a default character.

                                  * * *

        SYSOP   These are displayed to the sysop in the page window.

         BAR:   Displays a small bar graph growing in length.

     NUMERIC:   Uses numbers to display how many tries are remaining.
@ENDNODE
@NODE EG-3.0 "E!-PAGER v1.20 Documentation - Paging Sysop and Split Screen Chatting"

 PAGING SYSOP ============================================================

  When user selects the pager, he/she will be prompted for a reason, when
  the page begins selected page meter appears and screen possibly blinks.
  Sysop gets more action, sample player will be executed and a small win-
  dow opens to the default public screen with following button gadgets.

      SILENT:   Pressing this gadget will disable the sample player.

      ACCEPT:   Accept the chat request. User will be notified that sysop
                is coming soon to chat and the page is discontinued.

        CHAT:   Enters the selected chat mode and discontinues the page.

        DUMP:   Dump the chat request. User will be notified that you ha-
                ve no time to chat and the page is discontinued.


 SPLIT SCREEN CHAT =======================================================

  You may have used similar programs before, but for those who don't know
  what is a split screen chat - I'd recommend you run the chat and see it
  for your self. There are two separate windows, one for the user and the
  other window for person at the console.

  There are some very usefull commands listed under the credits, but main
  goal was to get the chat run smoothly even when both chatters are there
  writing text simultaneously. This can be very difficult with slower mo-
  dems because certain ANSI sequences are always needed, but speed should
  be very reasonable. Last two commands are for console only and will not
  show to the user online.

  Redraw, Clear, Beep and Quit are used for the obvious purposes. Command
  option is there for running global commands and CTRL-F does the same as
  normal DOS download would. Protect enabled user can only leave the chat
  by dropping carrier or when chatter at the console decides otherwise.

  Chat will automatically wrap words and scroll the screen when more room
  is required, currently there is no scroll back buffer. Size of the win-
  dows will be adjusted so they will fit to the screen properly. Any user
  with either less than 24 lines on the screen or a terminal lacking ANSI
  support will get the normal line chat automatically. You can also start
  chat with IPL codes from any text as it's an external C-Door.

  Unregistered version will always quit after one minute of chatting.
@ENDNODE
@NODE EG-4.0 "E!-PAGER v1.20 Documentation - External Utilities"

 OVERRIDER ===============================================================

  It is also possible to modify the availability settings without editing
  the configuration file. This is done with utility called Overrider. You
  can find executable called OVER from the binaries directory. If you run
  this without any parameters, small GUI will appear.

  SAVE and USE gadgets behave very much like with preferences utils. Data
  is only saved temporarily to the ENV: directory when you press USE, and
  also to the ENVARC: when you press SAVE button.

  Listview in the middle of the window is used to select predefined noti-
  ces that are displayed to the user before they enter their reason. KILL
  and ADD gadgets can be used to remove and add more entries and WRITE is
  used to save them to BBS:DATA/PagerNotice - you can also edit this file
  with your favourite text editor, each line contains one notice string.

  SYSOP LABEL string gadget is used to replace the default sysops name in
  the split screen chat. This is useful if you aren't at the console, and
  some friend of yours responds to chat requests. Mutually exclusive gad-
  get in the left corner of the window is simply used to override default
  configuration availability settings.

  There are also two pull-down menus with three items. I think only Snap-
  shot needs few lines of explanation. It will place GUI window's current
  dimensions to the memory so you can save them by pushing either SAVE or
  USE button. These dimensions are restored next time you run Overrider.

  You can also use Overrider from CLI. There are following arguments that
  can be used instead of the graphical user interface (herein referred as
  GUI). These commands can be used together and information not specified
  will remain as previously saved.

  -S     Normally information is only saved to ENV: directory, using this
         is going to save the changes to the ENVARC: as well.

  -A<X>  Availability mode to override the current setting. X can be:

         0: Sysop isn't available.
         1: Sysop should be available.
         2: Sysop wouldn't like to be disturbed.
         3: Default mode defined in the main configuration.

  -C<X>  X will be the new sysop label for the split screen chat.

  -N<X>  X will be the new notice, displayed to the user before page.


 NOTIFIERS ===============================================================

  There are situations when you come home and somebody still online paged
  you earlier and is waiting for you to come and chat. Reading the log is
  not very fast or easy way to check this out, small notifier window will
  be much more effective and sysop friendly.

  Pager executes a command after an unsuccesful page to open the notifier
  window containing the users name and the reason. There are two utilties
  in BIN directory for this features, OPEN to open the notifier and CLOSE
  to close it when you start a chat or when the user leaves. OPEN will be
  executed by the pager, path and name are defined in your configuration,
  CLOSE is executed using IPL codes from your language files.

  LANGUAGES/ENGLISH line 1392:

  \#2DOORS:PAGER/BIN/CLOSE\q1\n2\b1\c5Entering Chat Mode with the System Administrator.  Use ^C to exit.\n2

  LANGUAGES/ENGLISH line 1717:

  \#2DOORS:PAGER/BIN/CLOSE\q1\n1This session lasted \c7%d\q1 minutes.\n1

  The notifier window can also be closed by pressing the close gadget. If
  you don't wish to use notifiers you can simply use any nonexistent file
  name in the appropriate configuration entry and the nasty windows won't
  bother you anymore.
@ENDNODE
